  "event_preview": "Rockingham Speedway is a 0.940-mile (1.513 km) D-shaped oval in Rockingham, North Carolina, featuring 22–25 degrees of banking in the turns and 8 degrees on the straights. Opened in 1965, it hosted the NASCAR O'Reilly Auto Parts Series (then the Xfinity Series) from 1982 through 2004 before returning in 2025 for the first time in 21 years. The North Carolina Education Lottery 250 is the eighth race of the 2026 NASCAR O'Reilly Auto Parts Series season and only the second running of the event at the newly repaved circuit. The all-time qualifying lap record for the series at Rockingham belongs to Connor Zilisch, who turned a 22.630-second lap (149.536 mph) in April 2025. The fastest lap in race conditions - 23.41 seconds, set by Parker Retzlaff in that same 2025 race - remains the benchmark for race pace at The Rock.",
